x4freetext: Experimental and analysis
details
3.75 MV Van de Graaff accelerator
pulse width is less than 1 ns, repetition rate
250 kHz, average beam current 2.2  microAmp
Metallic Li target of about 1 mg/cm2
.Proton beam energy adjusted so to be 30 and 100 keV
above the 7-Li(p,n)7-Be reaction threshold 1.881 MeV
giving neutrons in energy ranges 3-100, 3-225 keV
experimental energy resolution 0.5 ns
.Standard sample Au-197, 15 mm diameter, 0.4 mm =
2.2470E-3 atoms/b thickness,weight 1.2987 gram,
enclosing aluminium canning 0.2662 gr
.Graphite sample 15 mm diameter, 1.5  mm = 1.3364E-2
atoms/b thickness, 0.4710 gram weight, enclosing
aluminium canning 0.3058 g
.Empty aluminium canning 0.2422 gram
.Corrections were made for multiple scattering,
for isotopic impurities, for neutron self-absorption,
for undetected events, for signal/background ratio -
all for different neutron energies
Last checking has been done.
SD: BIB update in all Subents.  In Subents
014 - 019: Col. EN-MEAN -> KT; values were changed.
ERR-ANALYS moved to Subents 2-27. EN-RSL deleted.
Averaged over
energy interval given in data section
.Absolute measurement
Flight path is 78.8 cm, resolution 1.2 ns/m
Karlsruhe 4pi-Ba-F2 detector consisting of
42 hexagonal and pentagonal crystals forming
a spherical Ba-F2 shell of 15 cm thickness and 10 cm
inner radius. Resolution is 7% at 2.5 MeV gamma
energy, peak efficiency  90 % at 1 MeV
.Cadmium metallic pellets
without canning,diameter 14.8 mm, thickness
1.7 mm(7.7312E-3 atoms/barn), weight 2.4978 gram.
Cd-110 content is 95.51%, Cd-111 content is  1.59%,
Cd-112 content is 13.26%, Cd-113 content is  0.50%,
Cd-114 content is  0.91%, Cd-116 content is  0.14%.
Data from table 5 of PR/C,66,(2),025801
Total error includes ERR-S, ERR-SYS
Total systematic error includes ERR-1 - ERR-7
Error due to flight path uncertainty
Error due to neutron flux normalization
Error due to sample mass and elemental
impurities
Error due to isotopic composition
Error due to isotopic correction
Error due to multiple scattering and self-
shielding in sample

x4freetext: .Maxwellian-averaged cross-sections were calculated
for energy interval 0-700 keV by dividing it into
three parts according cross-section`s sources.
The contribution I-1 was determined by normalizing the
cross sections of Kopecky (see REL-REF) to the present
data in the interval between 3 to 15 keV.
The dominant part I-2 between 3 and 225 keV is provided
by the present experiment. These data were obtained by
sufficient resolution in neutron energy to exclude
systematic uncertainties that may result in calculation
of the Maxwellian average if the energy grid is too
coarse.
At typical s-process temperatures the energy interval
from 225 to 700 keV contributes very little to the
Maxwellian average. For this part, the data of
Kopecky (see REL-REF) were normalized to the present
results between 50 and 225 keV.
